                     polymorphic field-visibility rule)

      Rule 3 - Conditional Field Rule (the polymorphic invariant):
        With party_type=Person, the UI Policy mandates:
          * <person> populated with a sys_user reference  (DONE BELOW:
            x_[scope]_demo_agent resolved by user_name lookup)
          * <organization> empty  (DONE BELOW: empty <organization/>
            element)
        The inverse pattern is exercised by parties 02, 05, and 07
        (party_type=Organization, organization populated, person
        empty). This file establishes the canonical Person-branch
        invariant for the LAST single-party demo case (case 09).

      Rule 4 - Reference resolution by stable human-readable key (AAP
              Section 0.7.2 "NO sys_id literals anywhere"):
        case   : <case display_value="CASE0000009">CASE0000009</case>
                 resolves to demo case 09 by the case table's
                 idempotent number lookup. CASE0000009 is the auto-
                 numbered value the platform generates for demo case 09
                 since cases 01 through 09 import in order with the
                 CASE0000001-format auto-number counter (case 01 ->
                 CASE0000001, case 02 -> CASE0000002, ..., case 09 ->
                 CASE0000009). This party's parent therefore resolves
                 to the demo case 09 record at
                 ../cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_09.xml.
        person : <person display_value="x_[scope]_demo_agent">
                 x_[scope]_demo_agent</person>  resolves to the demo
                 agent user by the sys_user table's user_name lookup.
                 The demo agent is the third-most-referenced demo user
