    Source-side semantic reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported)
    per AAP Section 0.8.1:
      acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-person-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/person/model/PersonAssociation.java
        ArkCase's PersonAssociation JPA entity declares fields including
        person (the source for our <person>; @ManyToOne to Person; we
        retype to a sys_user reference since ServiceNow's user model is
        the platform-canonical equivalent), parentId/parentType (the
        source for our <case> reference; ArkCase uses a generic parent-
        FK pattern with a discriminator string - we narrow this to a
        typed reference to x_[scope]_case since case_party is now
        single-purpose for case associations), personType (the source
        for our <role_label>; ArkCase models it as a free-form String
        column with no constraints; we preserve the same flexibility
        via String(100) but document Requester / Respondent / Witness
        as the canonical example values), notes (an optional ArkCase
        free-text annotation slot - intentionally OMITTED from our
        target schema per AAP Section 0.5.7), and tags (an
        @ElementCollection of String tags - intentionally OMITTED per
        AAP Section 0.5.7). ArkCase's single-table inheritance
        discriminator (cm_class_name) is collapsed in our target by
        the explicit party_type Choice field, which is the AAP-
        prescribed simplification of ArkCase's separate-table approach
        (acm_person_assoc + acm_person_org_assoc) into a single
        polymorphic table (x_[scope]_case_party). PersonOrganization
        Association.java is the secondary semantic source - its
        person + organization combined fields motivated our
        conditional person/organization invariant.

